description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; are recruiting for passionate, ambitious and committedAdult Nurses that are newly qualified or are due to qualify in 2021. Our bespoke preceptorship programme will support you to kick-start your career and allow you to be confident in what you love doing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elmleigh is in Havant and has wards for both men (Blue ward) and women (Red ward) with a functional mental illness - such as depression, a personality disorder or schizophrenia.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 34-bedded hospital provides care and treatment to people who are experiencing an acute mental health crisis and require a short period of hospital care to support their recovery. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The wards&#39; approach to care is ‘recovery-focused&#39; and delivered by a multi-disciplinary team made up of nursing staff, doctors, psychologists, health care support workers, occupational therapists and a chaplain.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Southern Health? What we will offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£24,907 to £30,615 pa based on full time hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;12 month bespokepreceptorship programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support with clinical skills and mandatory training, annual performance reviews and development reviews&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuing CPD development through our extensive trust education and training programmes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular monthly clinical &amp; management supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Free DBS and paid Update Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Company Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discount Card&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must meet the following:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relevant Nursing Degree - Either newly qualified or due to qualify in 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effective communication and strong impersonal skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compassionate and caring approach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team working skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be able to follow our values – Patients &amp; People First, Partnership and Respect&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent full time position, working 37.5 hours per week, covering a flexible shift pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more about what we can offer you at Southern Health or to book a tour to have a look around please contact eve.dennis@southernhealth.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
